1
00:00:03,440 --> 00:00:04,400
Oh no.
-What happened?

2
00:00:04,480 --> 00:00:05,600
Ugh, I broke a nail.

3
00:00:05,680 --> 00:00:08,760
Oh dear.
-What, are you making fun of me?

4
00:00:08,840 --> 00:00:11,040
I'm not making fun, I just don't know
how you'll deal with the loss.

5
00:00:11,680 --> 00:00:14,600
Very funny. I can't believe
I have to go to Lydia again.

6
00:00:14,680 --> 00:00:17,760
I sat with her for two hours yesterday.
Why does this have to happen to me?

7
00:00:17,840 --> 00:00:20,120
Why me?
-Like someone died.

8
00:00:20,200 --> 00:00:22,120
No, it's worse. Okay?
-Tragic.

9
00:00:22,880 --> 00:00:24,880
Now you'll have to deal
with the five stages of grief.

10
00:00:24,960 --> 00:00:27,400
It's not grief.
-See? It starts with denial,

11
00:00:27,480 --> 00:00:30,240
moves to anger, goes to bargaining,

12
00:00:30,600 --> 00:00:32,960
continues with depression, and ends with acceptance.

13
00:00:33,560 --> 00:00:35,720
It was tough, but you'll get through it with them.

14
00:00:36,800 --> 00:00:39,520
Yeah, you heard about the five stages
of how to shut you up?

15
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:43,760
It starts with a slap, goes to a smack, flick, punch,

16
00:00:44,160 --> 00:00:47,360
and finally a kick. It was tough,

17
00:00:47,760 --> 00:00:51,160
but we'll get through this with you. Right, girls?

18
00:00:58,120 --> 00:00:59,920
Look at me, look at me and...

19
00:01:09,760 --> 00:01:12,840
Shabbat Shalom.
-Hello, hello.

20
00:01:14,880 --> 00:01:16,200
Shabbat Shalom.

21
00:01:16,680 --> 00:01:17,800
Shabbat Shalom.

22
00:01:18,480 --> 00:01:21,400
Dad, you won't believe it. Dad, listen.

23
00:01:21,480 --> 00:01:24,120
We just won a scratch card downstairs, at Yossi's.

24
00:01:24,200 --> 00:01:28,320
How? It's Shabbat, closed.
-I found an unscratched scratch card on the sidewalk.

25
00:01:28,400 --> 00:01:31,240
What are you talking about? The chances of that happening

26
00:01:31,320 --> 00:01:34,680
are like... winning the lottery.
-Exactly. We won.

27
00:01:35,240 --> 00:01:36,880
No way.
-Yes way!

28
00:01:36,960 --> 00:01:38,160
For 2,500 shekels.

29
00:01:38,240 --> 00:01:40,720
No way.
-Yes way.

30
00:01:41,680 --> 00:01:45,440
I've been scratching with him for twenty years,
never won even once.

31
00:01:46,320 --> 00:01:49,560
That's Shani's hand.
She scratched with the nail she broke...

32
00:01:50,120 --> 00:01:52,840
Honey, bring me a scratch card
faster, faster.

33
00:01:52,920 --> 00:01:54,480
What a hand. Gold.

34
00:01:55,520 --> 00:01:56,840
Give me the card.
-Here you go.

35
00:01:57,360 --> 00:01:58,360
What's this, honey?

36
00:01:58,920 --> 00:02:01,800
They gave it to us at school and I forgot to show you.

37
00:02:02,360 --> 00:02:05,240
It's the registration form for classes.
-How much will it actually cost

38
00:02:05,320 --> 00:02:07,000
to send the girl to classes now?

39
00:02:09,160 --> 00:02:10,360
2,500 shekels.

40
00:02:11,600 --> 00:02:14,280
No way.
-Yes way.

41
00:02:23,200 --> 00:02:25,840
Ben, D.
-He'll definitely call.

42
00:02:25,920 --> 00:02:29,240
Ben, D, Meirav. Come on, better one.

43
00:02:29,320 --> 00:02:33,200
Don't say that. He'll come back.
-But he said he wouldn't.

44
00:02:34,200 --> 00:02:37,360
But he'll come back.
-Meirav, why can't you accept that?

45
00:02:37,440 --> 00:02:40,080
At least he was nice enough to tell you to your face.

46
00:02:40,160 --> 00:02:43,000
He won't come back.
-I'm telling you he will.

47
00:02:43,080 --> 00:02:45,080
I'll call him.
-No, Meirav. He told you

48
00:02:45,160 --> 00:02:48,720
under no circumstances to call him.
-Shabbat Shalom. You're not calling him!

49
00:02:49,960 --> 00:02:51,360
Who did Grandma miss? Who?

50
00:02:52,120 --> 00:02:54,520
I just finished making the mezilof.

51
00:02:54,880 --> 00:02:59,040
I don't want to. Mom, I don't want mezilof.
-Neither do I.

52
00:03:00,440 --> 00:03:02,160
What do you mean? What does "don't want mezilof" mean?

53
00:03:02,800 --> 00:03:03,760
Girls, go play.

54
00:03:07,240 --> 00:03:09,000
What happened?
-No, what a coincidence.

55
00:03:09,960 --> 00:03:13,720
Shai brought mezilof from the supermarket.
-Mezilof?

56
00:03:14,440 --> 00:03:16,400
Yeah, like this industrial mezilof.

57
00:03:17,120 --> 00:03:20,160
Mezilof in a box?
-Yeah.

58
00:03:20,560 --> 00:03:23,280
He actually brought it on Tuesday.
By Thursday, there was nothing left.

59
00:03:23,640 --> 00:03:26,480
It's not as good as yours. Right?
That's obvious. There's no comparison at all,

60
00:03:26,560 --> 00:03:29,560
but the kids actually liked it.
-Industrial mezilof?

61
00:03:30,480 --> 00:03:33,040
Are you making fun of me?
-No, really, Mom.

62
00:03:33,120 --> 00:03:34,800
He brought this from the supermarket's freezer.

63
00:03:34,880 --> 00:03:37,000
It’s not fresh, but... frozen like that.

64
00:03:39,320 --> 00:03:40,160
Quiet!
-What happened?

65
00:03:40,240 --> 00:03:41,080
It’s fresh.

66
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:43,560
I told you he would call.

67
00:03:44,760 --> 00:03:48,480
Hey. Which phone are you calling from?
I don’t recognize this number.

68
00:03:49,520 --> 00:03:50,920
Oh..

69
00:03:51,920 --> 00:03:52,760
Mistake.

70
00:03:55,200 --> 00:03:57,040
Here, look at the card.

71
00:03:57,120 --> 00:03:59,360
No, this isn’t real, it’s a nightmare.

72
00:03:59,440 --> 00:04:01,600
Twenty that... I’m saying

73
00:04:02,360 --> 00:04:05,040
I told you, there’s no way you’ll win.

74
00:04:05,800 --> 00:04:08,120
He has a curse on his little booth.

75
00:04:09,960 --> 00:04:12,960
Shabbat Shalom.
-Shabbat Shalom.

76
00:04:16,920 --> 00:04:19,000
What’s with that face? Did you lose a scratch card?

77
00:04:19,399 --> 00:04:22,079
What?
-He got the test results

78
00:04:22,400 --> 00:04:24,040
and he doesn’t want to open them.
-Alin, enough.

79
00:04:24,800 --> 00:04:27,000
On the phone?
-By email.

80
00:04:27,080 --> 00:04:28,840
Come on, just open it already.
-I don’t want to!

81
00:04:28,920 --> 00:04:31,560
What is this? What are "the results"?
-Of those tests,

82
00:04:31,640 --> 00:04:35,200
that they told you about on Friday.
-Why did you even go for that test?

83
00:04:35,280 --> 00:04:36,480
I didn’t want to. Alin forced me.

84
00:04:36,560 --> 00:04:39,760
Here, now it’s official. The result is positive.

85
00:04:39,840 --> 00:04:42,840
No way, that’s not true.
-Look for yourself.

86
00:04:42,920 --> 00:04:46,400
It must be a mistake, it’s someone else’s, it’s not true!

87
00:04:49,640 --> 00:04:50,640
I get it.

88
00:04:51,080 --> 00:04:52,200
Poor guy. In denial.

89
00:04:53,800 --> 00:04:57,040
The things people come up with these days.
No, I can’t believe it.

90
00:04:57,840 --> 00:05:01,920
A frozen yogurt at the supermarket.
That’s the weirdest thing I’ve ever heard.

91
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:06,120
Yeah, it’s from "Mamazlof."
Shai is already waiting for the "Mamachalata" to come out.

92
00:05:06,200 --> 00:05:07,360
So wait, they put it in the freezers?

93
00:05:08,400 --> 00:05:10,000
How funny.

94
00:05:10,480 --> 00:05:13,600
It’ll never work for them,
it won’t work. It’s not economical. No way!

95
00:05:13,680 --> 00:05:14,520
No way.

96
00:05:14,600 --> 00:05:16,800
I understand a thing or two.
It won’t catch on. Never.

97
00:05:17,480 --> 00:05:20,960
It can never beat
home-cooked food. Never.

98
00:05:21,040 --> 00:05:24,160
Of course not, Mom. Of course.
-Never.

99
00:05:24,240 --> 00:05:26,160
Shhh...
-What’s up? What happened?

100
00:05:27,320 --> 00:05:28,840
I thought the phone was vibrating.

101
00:05:30,640 --> 00:05:31,760
14

102
00:05:34,800 --> 00:05:36,840
Shabbat Shalom.
-Shabbat Shalom.

103
00:05:36,920 --> 00:05:38,840
Shabbat Shalom.
-What happened?

104
00:05:40,200 --> 00:05:43,000
There was a mess with the computer.
-What did you do to it now?

105
00:05:43,560 --> 00:05:44,920
Why me?
-So who?

106
00:05:45,400 --> 00:05:48,040
She accidentally deleted the folders
of our photos on the computer.

107
00:05:48,400 --> 00:05:50,240
What a sad story, Silvan.

108
00:05:51,160 --> 00:05:52,840
Sit down, can you bring the letter for a sec?

109
00:05:54,920 --> 00:05:57,400
Did you check the name of the sender?
Because he’s had a mess like this before.

110
00:05:57,480 --> 00:05:59,320
Come on, that’s your daughter’s name.

111
00:05:59,400 --> 00:06:00,520
Yeah.

112
00:06:00,600 --> 00:06:02,040
Maybe last year’s date?

113
00:06:02,120 --> 00:06:02,960
No.

114
00:06:04,400 --> 00:06:07,480
Honey...
-Everything’s fine, Moshe.

115
00:06:07,560 --> 00:06:09,600
We can recover it, I know we can.

116
00:06:09,680 --> 00:06:11,120
I don’t know. Did you hear what Coral said?

117
00:06:11,960 --> 00:06:14,320
What does Coral know?
There are people who are experts in these things.

118
00:06:15,040 --> 00:06:17,280
Coral is an expert.
-Not just a school kid.

119
00:06:17,360 --> 00:06:20,520
An expert, like a real expert.
-They’re the biggest experts out there, for real.

120
00:06:21,080 --> 00:06:23,480
Moshe, we can recover it. I know we can.

121
00:06:24,240 --> 00:06:26,000
I don’t know, babe, I don’t know.

122
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:34,880
Don’t tell me “I don’t know, babe.”
-Babe...

123
00:06:34,960 --> 00:06:36,240
And don’t call me “babe.”

124
00:06:36,320 --> 00:06:39,240
And don’t tell me it can’t be recovered.
Who are you to say that to me?

125
00:06:39,320 --> 00:06:42,160
Why, do you understand computers?
If you were such a computer whiz,

126
00:06:42,240 --> 00:06:45,160
you’d upload the pictures
from the camera to the computer every time.

127
00:06:45,240 --> 00:06:48,240
But you don’t know how to do that, right?
I know how to do it, right?

128
00:06:48,320 --> 00:06:50,320
I don’t get this stuff.
You know I don’t get...

129
00:06:50,400 --> 00:06:53,600
It’s all your fault. Everything.
What am I supposed to do now, huh?

130
00:06:53,680 --> 00:06:56,480
All our history is gone, everything is gone, everything.

131
00:06:56,560 --> 00:06:59,880
And that technician... is she a computer expert?

132
00:06:59,960 --> 00:07:03,800
What does she know? Did she even study anything?
Does she know anything about life?

133
00:07:04,120 --> 00:07:07,920
Does she know anything about our whole lives that got erased?

134
00:07:08,240 --> 00:07:11,720
This is the last time
she’s coming to the Knesset. The last time.

135
00:07:13,240 --> 00:07:16,080
This is just outrageous. 2,500 shekels?
-Come on, isn’t that way more

136
00:07:16,160 --> 00:07:17,040
than what we paid last year?

137
00:07:17,120 --> 00:07:19,120
Thieves.
-They have no shame. And for what?

138
00:07:19,200 --> 00:07:20,080
Really, for what?

139
00:07:20,160 --> 00:07:22,720
They only have numbers in their heads.
-And the girl, she’s not learning anything there,

140
00:07:22,800 --> 00:07:25,040
she’s not learning anything there.
-Nothing. You just give,

141
00:07:25,120 --> 00:07:27,680
you don’t get anything back.
-And another 2,500 shekels?

142
00:07:27,760 --> 00:07:30,920
They’re brainwashing the kids with math
like it’s the most important thing in the world.

143
00:07:31,000 --> 00:07:33,240
Babe, it’s for extracurriculars.
-So that makes it even worse.

144
00:07:33,320 --> 00:07:36,360
At least if they took the money,
they’d invest it in math, like they should.

145
00:07:36,440 --> 00:07:38,320
The girl doesn’t even know her times tables by heart.
-Right.

146
00:07:38,400 --> 00:07:41,520
You know that in enlightened countries
the state pays for those extracurriculars

147
00:07:41,600 --> 00:07:44,560
to ensure the future of its citizens.
-Everything costs in this country.

148
00:07:44,640 --> 00:07:46,160
You don’t get anything back.
-Exactly. As if we don’t have

149
00:07:46,240 --> 00:07:49,120
anything to do with that money,
as if we don’t have other needs and expenses.

150
00:07:49,200 --> 00:07:52,400
No, this isn’t real. You know
what we could buy with 2,500 shekels?

151
00:07:52,480 --> 00:07:54,560
A floor vacuum.
-A 24-inch computer monitor.

152
00:07:54,640 --> 00:07:57,920
Excuse me, a floor vacuum?
-Excuse me, a 24-inch computer monitor?

153
00:08:00,520 --> 00:08:03,280
Call! Please, call.

154
00:08:04,200 --> 00:08:05,840
Auntie, why are you sad?

155
00:08:06,520 --> 00:08:07,520
Oh, my dear,

156
00:08:08,160 --> 00:08:12,680
yeah, I’m a bit sad. You see,
sometimes adults feel pain in their hearts.

157
00:08:13,320 --> 00:08:16,400
You know when you give
your all to someone,

158
00:08:16,480 --> 00:08:19,760
put your heart and soul in their hands,
and what do they do with it?

159
00:08:19,840 --> 00:08:22,000
They throw it away, like it means nothing,

160
00:08:22,080 --> 00:08:23,720
to the time and experiences we shared together.

161
00:08:25,320 --> 00:08:27,640
You know we barely went on a second date?

162
00:08:27,720 --> 00:08:29,800
And he even tells me, “Don’t call me anymore.”

163
00:08:29,880 --> 00:08:32,240
He tells me I won’t call him anymore.

164
00:08:32,320 --> 00:08:34,919
That he won’t call me anymore.
Who needs him anyway?

165
00:08:35,000 --> 00:08:38,039
To cut it off like that, so coldly?
Not even let me say a word?

166
00:08:38,840 --> 00:08:41,919
There’s no way in the world
I’d agree to be with a guy like that.

167
00:08:42,600 --> 00:08:44,280
And I even thought he’d be a husband.

168
00:08:45,560 --> 00:08:46,720
He’s not worthy of me.

169
00:08:47,280 --> 00:08:48,360
Why did you ask her?

170
00:08:49,680 --> 00:08:50,600
What?

171
00:08:57,200 --> 00:09:01,720
Rachel, I swear to you.
I don’t understand what you’re angry about.

172
00:09:02,280 --> 00:09:05,600
They did a mess-up, Silvan. A mess-up.

173
00:09:06,080 --> 00:09:09,960
Yeah, but... they managed to stick
a human ear on a mouse’s back.

174
00:09:10,920 --> 00:09:14,360
They can’t do a mess-up?
-It’s all the big companies,

175
00:09:14,440 --> 00:09:16,560
it’s just money, money, money.

176
00:09:16,640 --> 00:09:19,400
And sell, sell as much as possible.

177
00:09:19,480 --> 00:09:23,200
I wouldn’t be surprised if we soon
see ads for mess-ups on TV.

178
00:09:23,280 --> 00:09:26,960
Well, that’s already in the freezers at the supermarket.
So why wouldn’t Mrs. Feigold

179
00:09:27,040 --> 00:09:30,240
buy and serve a mess-up?
-So let her buy...

180
00:09:30,320 --> 00:09:34,200
Mrs. Feigold, let her buy.
I still don’t understand what your problem is.

181
00:09:34,280 --> 00:09:36,520
What's the problem? She doesn't know how to make it.

182
00:09:36,840 --> 00:09:39,040
That's the issue. It's outrageous.

183
00:09:39,120 --> 00:09:41,360
No respect for tradition. Nothing, nothing.

184
00:09:41,440 --> 00:09:44,440
They make it in a factory, Silvan, in a factory.

185
00:09:44,520 --> 00:09:47,440
This is poison. Who knows what they put in there?

186
00:09:47,520 --> 00:09:49,280
I'm sure there's supervision on it.

187
00:09:49,360 --> 00:09:53,960
I'm sure it's under rabbinical supervision.
Come on, don't get carried away. It's just junk...

188
00:09:54,040 --> 00:09:56,000
And Shai, how can he not be embarrassed?

189
00:09:56,080 --> 00:09:57,720
He, more than anyone, should know better.

190
00:09:58,680 --> 00:10:01,360
Why, does he make it?
-No, he buys it.

191
00:10:01,440 --> 00:10:04,800
He buys it.
You can't put all the love,

192
00:10:04,880 --> 00:10:10,200
all the patience, all the values
into something that comes from a machine, Silvan,

193
00:10:10,280 --> 00:10:13,040
a machine. You can't. It's machines, it's...

194
00:10:13,720 --> 00:10:15,520
No need for humans, none. No need for humans.

195
00:10:15,600 --> 00:10:18,880
A robot. A robot makes your junk, Silvan.

196
00:10:19,360 --> 00:10:21,800
A robot. Not a human. A robot.

197
00:10:21,880 --> 00:10:23,840
Enough, relax, relax.

198
00:10:23,920 --> 00:10:28,200
Why? Why? Why am I losing my hair?

199
00:10:28,280 --> 00:10:30,040
That's just how it is, babe.
-But why?

200
00:10:30,120 --> 00:10:33,360
I'm asking myself why too.
-You won't believe how mad I am, Alin.

201
00:10:33,440 --> 00:10:36,040
I can't believe you're mad
about things you can't change.

202
00:10:36,120 --> 00:10:38,080
And it's not just me, Alin.
-Am I losing my hair too?

203
00:10:38,160 --> 00:10:42,160
Stop making fun of me, okay? We're also talking
about genes I'm supposed to pass to my kid.

204
00:10:42,240 --> 00:10:44,480
For heaven's sake, he's three weeks old,

205
00:10:44,560 --> 00:10:46,800
now he's going to be bald too.
-He’s already bald.

206
00:10:46,880 --> 00:10:49,640
Not now. When he grows up.
-Come on, really.

207
00:10:50,920 --> 00:10:52,600
What's the point? What's the point?

208
00:10:52,680 --> 00:10:54,760
I won't accept that.
-I don't think they’re asking you.

209
00:10:56,440 --> 00:10:58,800
Excuse me.
-I won't accept that, Alin. Okay?

210
00:10:58,880 --> 00:10:59,720
You're right. You're right.

211
00:11:07,880 --> 00:11:10,240
I’m not willing to lose all our history
with one "delete."

212
00:11:10,320 --> 00:11:12,440
No way, Moshe—
-There's nothing to be done, babe.

213
00:11:12,520 --> 00:11:14,080
Is it about money?
-No.

214
00:11:14,160 --> 00:11:15,440
If it's about money, I'll borrow from Shai.

215
00:11:15,520 --> 00:11:18,720
But it's not about money, Beshmat.
-Call Coral again,

216
00:11:18,800 --> 00:11:21,000
see what she says.
-But you've already talked to her, honey.

217
00:11:21,080 --> 00:11:23,240
I talked. But sorry, it hurts me too.

218
00:11:23,320 --> 00:11:25,520
You heard what she said.
You can't retrieve it from the hard disk,

219
00:11:25,600 --> 00:11:28,000
you can't.
-But maybe there's something we can do,

220
00:11:28,080 --> 00:11:31,280
maybe, maybe, call her again,
tell her I'm willing to pay any amount,

221
00:11:31,360 --> 00:11:33,560
just to get our photos back.
We'll recommend her to so many people,

222
00:11:33,640 --> 00:11:37,040
we'll send her clients. Moshe, we'll give her
a like on Facebook, whatever she wants.

223
00:11:37,120 --> 00:11:40,240
But Beshmat, I'm explaining to you.
No, no, no. It's impossible.

224
00:11:40,320 --> 00:11:41,200
It's impossible.

225
00:11:42,760 --> 00:11:44,080
But I want you to talk to them.

226
00:11:45,760 --> 00:11:47,840
Talk to who?
To the robots from "Mamzelof"? Who?

227
00:11:47,920 --> 00:11:50,840
No, to the kids. I want you to tell them

228
00:11:51,240 --> 00:11:53,240
that you're not okay with them buying it anymore.

229
00:11:54,120 --> 00:11:56,560
Why? Why should I say that to them?

230
00:11:56,640 --> 00:11:58,440
Because you don't know what's inside.

231
00:12:01,360 --> 00:12:03,280
Junk... they put in date syrup.

232
00:12:03,360 --> 00:12:07,560
Yeah, and maybe it's poison?
-I can't say that to them.

233
00:12:07,640 --> 00:12:10,160
They want to eat it
even during the week. What's your problem?

234
00:12:10,960 --> 00:12:13,120
Fine, then I'll make it for them
and they'll take it home.

235
00:12:14,840 --> 00:12:16,120
Junk?
-Yeah.

236
00:12:16,200 --> 00:12:19,520
For all I care, they can
freeze it and thaw it out.

237
00:12:19,600 --> 00:12:21,720
They can also, for all I care,
say they bought it at the supermarket.

238
00:12:21,800 --> 00:12:24,920
Just let me make it and you go
tell them not to buy it anymore.

239
00:12:25,840 --> 00:12:26,760
Go. Now.

240
00:12:28,080 --> 00:12:29,680
I... just don't feel good right now.

241
00:12:29,760 --> 00:12:30,600
Silvan!

242
00:12:33,960 --> 00:12:36,200
Please, God, help me.
-Help me.

243
00:12:36,280 --> 00:12:39,200
I'm ready to do anything, please.
-Get a transplant.

244
00:12:39,280 --> 00:12:41,840
Just give me a few more weeks,
I promise to do whatever it takes.

245
00:12:42,400 --> 00:12:44,200
Sure.
-I'll start exercising.

246
00:12:44,800 --> 00:12:45,840
Right.
-Come on.

247
00:12:47,840 --> 00:12:48,680
I'll put on tefillin.

248
00:12:51,440 --> 00:12:53,320
Eat right and healthy.

249
00:12:53,400 --> 00:12:55,080
I'm even willing to give up sex.

250
00:12:56,560 --> 00:12:59,240
That's enough. What happened to you?

251
00:12:59,800 --> 00:13:02,120
It was fine, honey, it was fine.

252
00:13:02,840 --> 00:13:05,680
Great, Orna. Just who I was looking for.
You're good with words.

253
00:13:05,760 --> 00:13:07,920
Meirav, we're just...
-Shut up for a second.

254
00:13:08,000 --> 00:13:11,600
I need you to call Ra'ban
and convince him to call me back.

255
00:13:11,680 --> 00:13:14,840
What?
-Ra'ban. We went out this week and he decided to break up.

256
00:13:15,400 --> 00:13:18,480
Another one bites the dust.
-Moshe, if you're not helping, at least be quiet.

257
00:13:18,560 --> 00:13:21,040
I'm in the kitchen. Is there any majluf left?
-Check for yourself.

258
00:13:22,400 --> 00:13:24,160
I don't want to get angry anymore.

259
00:13:24,640 --> 00:13:27,640
That's the number. Call from your phone.

260
00:13:28,600 --> 00:13:31,240
What do you want me to tell him?
-I don't really care.

261
00:13:31,320 --> 00:13:36,000
But it has to be in your words.
Explain to him why he should come back to me.

262
00:13:36,080 --> 00:13:38,160
Why?
-I don't know.

263
00:13:38,960 --> 00:13:41,960
Because I'm here! Sexy and confident.

264
00:13:42,040 --> 00:13:45,160
And I have a huge heart, and if he comes back,
he can enjoy all of that.

265
00:13:45,240 --> 00:13:47,360
No, why do you want me to call?

266
00:13:48,080 --> 00:13:50,000
I'm afraid he won't answer my call.

267
00:13:51,280 --> 00:13:54,760
Tell him it's a shame if he doesn't come back
and that I promise, promise

268
00:13:54,840 --> 00:13:58,120
that I won't ever talk about family and kids again. For now.

269
00:13:58,760 --> 00:14:02,200
And that I won't wait for him under the house anymore.
I promise, promise.

270
00:14:04,680 --> 00:14:08,400
There's no way in the world you're going to convince me
that you need a new computer screen right now.

271
00:14:08,480 --> 00:14:10,480
You're not telling me we're buying a floor vacuum.

272
00:14:10,840 --> 00:14:13,440
Oh, I absolutely am, and here I am saying it:

273
00:14:14,080 --> 00:14:17,440
We'll have a floor vacuum
long before we get a new computer screen.

274
00:14:17,520 --> 00:14:18,640
Oh, like that?
-Yeah.

275
00:14:18,720 --> 00:14:19,600
So now, principle,

276
00:14:19,680 --> 00:14:21,560
I'm going to buy a computer screen.
-I want to see.

277
00:14:21,640 --> 00:14:22,560
Please, you'll see.
-Yeah.

278
00:14:22,640 --> 00:14:26,520
Mom, did you sign the form for me?
-Oh, no, no, sweetie.

279
00:14:26,600 --> 00:14:27,600
I already signed it.

280
00:14:36,040 --> 00:14:39,520
I forgot about those classes.
-2,500 shekels.

281
00:14:41,280 --> 00:14:42,480
Gone.

282
00:14:50,240 --> 00:14:53,080
You see, it’s not about that vacuum, but when I scratched it

283
00:14:53,160 --> 00:14:56,360
and suddenly saw I won,
I felt special.

284
00:14:56,440 --> 00:14:59,360
Me too, I just want to win something...

285
00:15:00,440 --> 00:15:02,520
Not the costume contest at work.

286
00:15:03,160 --> 00:15:04,560
And I don't want them to take it away from me after five minutes.

287
00:15:05,520 --> 00:15:08,320
And here, not even five minutes have passed.
-To me, it feels like forever.

288
00:15:09,000 --> 00:15:11,840
It's not fair. Just when we win something
once in our lives,

289
00:15:11,920 --> 00:15:14,280
we have to give it up.
What, don't we deserve to win?

290
00:15:14,760 --> 00:15:19,400
And it's not that I wanted a screen, I wanted the freedom
to buy myself whatever I want.

291
00:15:19,480 --> 00:15:21,760
Exactly. I'm the same way.

292
00:15:21,840 --> 00:15:24,360
Even though I really wanted a vacuum.
-I know, honey.

293
00:15:24,440 --> 00:15:27,200
We really need it, yeah.
-I know, honey. You're right.

294
00:15:27,280 --> 00:15:28,240
I'm sorry.

295
00:15:29,080 --> 00:15:32,920
Next time we win, no, no, no,
I'll buy you a computer screen right away.

296
00:15:34,760 --> 00:15:37,000
It hurts so much.
-Seriously, what a bummer.

297
00:15:43,040 --> 00:15:45,960
It hurts so much.
-Like a hole in my heart.

298
00:15:46,960 --> 00:15:49,720
All our history, my little family's history.

299
00:15:50,200 --> 00:15:52,040
And ours. Oh, Ra'ban...

300
00:15:52,120 --> 00:15:55,400
It's okay to cry. Let it out! Everything out, everything.

301
00:15:55,480 --> 00:15:58,880
That's it, it's all gone, everything.
The big birthday party,

302
00:15:58,960 --> 00:16:03,920
the hotel in Eilat, the trip to Bodrum...
-the first date, the second date...

303
00:16:04,000 --> 00:16:06,640
I thought there was only one date.
-I count the time

304
00:16:06,720 --> 00:16:09,680
he caught me in the stairwell! - a date.

305
00:16:10,240 --> 00:16:13,080
Caught you in the stairwell?
-Just once.

306
00:16:13,960 --> 00:16:16,040
That's it. It's all gone. Everything's gone.

307
00:16:16,120 --> 00:16:20,040
He’s gone.
-I don’t see how I’ll get over this.

308
00:16:20,120 --> 00:16:22,320
I don’t feel like doing anything.
-Me neither.

309
00:16:23,360 --> 00:16:26,720
I don’t even have an appetite.
-Yeah, it’s like food has no taste.

310
00:16:26,800 --> 00:16:27,680
Cheers.

311
00:16:31,440 --> 00:16:34,280
Cry, cry, cry.

312
00:16:36,400 --> 00:16:39,440
There were no tissues. That’s what happened.
-Thanks.

313
00:16:41,680 --> 00:16:43,680
Come on, Rachel, why like this, Rachel?

314
00:16:44,240 --> 00:16:46,280
Rachel, why like this? Come on.

315
00:16:46,800 --> 00:16:48,680
I've lost my charm, Sali.

316
00:16:49,920 --> 00:16:53,040
That’s what they say, right? I’m no longer useful.

317
00:16:53,120 --> 00:16:56,000
Come on, please, Rachel,

318
00:16:57,160 --> 00:16:59,680
it’s just a little crying. Just... relax...

319
00:16:59,760 --> 00:17:05,680
No, there’s no more of Grandma’s crying,
no more of Rachel’s crying,

320
00:17:05,760 --> 00:17:07,119
no more Rachels
-Enough, enough.

321
00:17:07,200 --> 00:17:10,400
That’s it, no more Rachel.
-Enough, my sweet. Enough.

322
00:17:14,160 --> 00:17:17,720
No. I’m not useful. Why would they come to visit? Why?

323
00:17:17,800 --> 00:17:22,280
Why? They waited all week for the crying.
It used to be like that.

324
00:17:22,720 --> 00:17:26,079
Enough, my sweet, enough, enough. Here.
-Come on, enough already, enough, enough.

325
00:17:26,160 --> 00:17:29,280
Go get me a tissue from the bedroom.
It’s making my nose red.

326
00:17:29,360 --> 00:17:30,840
Okay, I’m not feeling well. Okay.

327
00:17:34,320 --> 00:17:36,680
It makes me sad, you understand?
-Of course I understand.

328
00:17:38,000 --> 00:17:39,840
I know you love me no matter what,

329
00:17:39,920 --> 00:17:42,960
I’ll always be beautiful in your eyes. But, but...

330
00:17:43,040 --> 00:17:45,280
It’s my hair and it’s like my masculinity.

331
00:17:45,960 --> 00:17:49,000
There’s also that story in the Bible
about Samson and Delilah and his hair,

332
00:17:49,080 --> 00:17:52,800
and what does that say about me? That I’m getting old?

333
00:17:54,240 --> 00:17:57,720
Hey, what’s up? What happened? What’s with the gloom?
-His hair.

334
00:17:58,280 --> 00:17:59,320
Forget it, you won’t understand.

335
00:18:12,720 --> 00:18:15,760
Come on, babe, I signed for you and I’ll send you
a check on Monday to school. Okay?

336
00:18:15,840 --> 00:18:17,520
Thanks.
-Did you eat?

337
00:18:17,600 --> 00:18:22,360
I was hungry, so I ate Grandma’s crying
and it was way tastier.

338
00:18:22,440 --> 00:18:25,840
Tell Dad not to buy that one anymore.
-Okay, babe. I’ll tell him.

339
00:18:25,920 --> 00:18:28,480
Did you hear that? Did you hear?

340
00:18:30,400 --> 00:18:34,520
And besides, I, I will always,
always need you. Okay?

341
00:18:35,000 --> 00:18:37,240
Enough.
-Look at them.

342
00:18:37,720 --> 00:18:40,600
What, is this a photo moment? Oops, sorry.

343
00:18:41,080 --> 00:18:42,880
It’s okay.
-I’m such a fool.

344
00:18:43,640 --> 00:18:44,760
I know that hurts too.

345
00:18:45,320 --> 00:18:48,080
I promise you we’ll create our own
new history,

346
00:18:48,160 --> 00:18:50,400
exactly the same as it was.
-Really?

347
00:18:50,480 --> 00:18:51,560
Does that mean we’ll go to Bodrum again?

348
00:18:53,080 --> 00:18:56,480
Yeah, even though the situation with Turkey isn’t what it used to be.
-Doesn’t matter.

349
00:18:59,680 --> 00:19:03,360
Luckily, it’s trendy.
I can point out a bunch of bald guys

350
00:19:03,440 --> 00:19:05,800
who aren’t ashamed of their baldness.
-Right, and it’s sexy.

351
00:19:06,360 --> 00:19:08,680
Oh, relax, babe. That bald guy is mine.

352
00:19:08,760 --> 00:19:09,760
Go find someone else. Go find another bald guy.

353
00:19:10,320 --> 00:19:13,040
Alright, whatever will be, will be. I know...
-It’ll be fine.

354
00:19:14,560 --> 00:19:17,480
Oh, excuse me, there’s another bald guy who needs me.

355
00:19:20,520 --> 00:19:22,000
So what, we’re growing up?

356
00:19:23,480 --> 00:19:24,440
Wait until you get to the white hair.

357
00:19:25,600 --> 00:19:26,880
Alin...

358
00:19:29,080 --> 00:19:31,480
What a thief. So what?

359
00:19:31,560 --> 00:19:34,480
So he already saw we’re the kind that doesn’t just win the lottery.

360
00:19:35,000 --> 00:19:37,600
We’re the kind that goes bald
and works hard for our money.

361
00:19:38,240 --> 00:19:39,200
Yeah.

362
00:19:39,800 --> 00:19:42,400
Next time I win something,
I’ll buy you a screen right away.

363
00:19:42,960 --> 00:19:44,520
24-inch floor vacuum.

364
00:19:45,520 --> 00:19:48,600
Sis, you hear? I got the bonus from work,

365
00:19:48,680 --> 00:19:51,120
so now I can pay you back
the 2,500 shekels I owe you.

366
00:19:52,320 --> 00:19:53,160
Thanks.

367
00:19:54,360 --> 00:19:55,440
Don’t even think about it.

368
00:19:56,280 --> 00:19:57,160
Who’s thinking?

369
00:20:00,920 --> 00:20:03,000
So what? Saturday’s tough, huh?

370
00:20:04,800 --> 00:20:06,240
Mom, is there any slice of zelif left?

371
00:20:07,160 --> 00:20:09,840
I saved you a piece, my boy.
-Oh, champ.

372
00:20:10,520 --> 00:20:14,520
So what’s new with the Hasson family?
-I hope Meirav gets better.

373
00:20:15,120 --> 00:20:17,680
I don’t get it.
They only went on one date, right?

374
00:20:17,760 --> 00:20:19,880
Yeah, yeah.
-Shabbat Shalom.

375
00:20:19,960 --> 00:20:22,560
Shabbat Shalom.
-Shabbat Shalom.

376
00:20:22,640 --> 00:20:24,880
That’s it, I’m done mourning that guy.

377
00:20:24,960 --> 00:20:27,840
Mourning?
-Yeah, yeah, there are five stages of grief.

378
00:20:27,920 --> 00:20:30,280
And Shai knows them all.

379
00:20:30,360 --> 00:20:33,920
Denial, anger, bargaining, depression...
-and acceptance.

380
00:20:34,960 --> 00:20:38,320
So you’ve accepted?
-Of course. Fresh start behind me.

381
00:20:38,400 --> 00:20:40,320
I hope you learned something from it at least.

382
00:20:40,400 --> 00:20:42,920
For sure. I won’t build castles in the air anymore.

383
00:20:43,000 --> 00:20:46,800
When I was a kid, I always tried
to build castles with blocks,

384
00:20:46,880 --> 00:20:48,680
and they always fell...
-Not now.

385
00:20:48,760 --> 00:20:49,800
Sorry.

386
00:20:49,880 --> 00:20:52,240
Next time, I don’t have to describe
how our kids will look on the first date,

387
00:20:52,320 --> 00:20:55,320
the wedding dress,

388
00:20:55,400 --> 00:20:58,800
the dress for the party, and the dress for the Shabbat Chatan.

389
00:21:05,200 --> 00:21:06,440
What’s that?
-Hungry.

390
00:21:06,520 --> 00:21:08,320
Hey, could my laptop be with you?

391
00:21:08,400 --> 00:21:11,840
Yeah. Oops, your laptop is with me.

392
00:21:12,640 --> 00:21:14,160
It happens. Come on up.

393
00:21:14,840 --> 00:21:17,240
You took his computer?
-It happens.

394
00:21:17,320 --> 00:21:19,120
Okay, I’m asking all of you to clear the living room.

395
00:21:19,200 --> 00:21:20,520
What?
-What now?

396
00:21:20,600 --> 00:21:21,840
What’s not clear?

397
00:21:21,920 --> 00:21:23,480
He came to offer him perfume.

398
00:21:24,080 --> 00:21:25,520
Come on! Seriously!

399
00:21:30,600 --> 00:21:32,480
I don’t think Meirav has moved past denial.

400
00:21:32,560 --> 00:21:35,680
And you haven’t moved past bargaining.
-Me? You.

401
00:21:35,760 --> 00:21:37,920
And you’ve slipped into denial.
-Okay, fine.

402
00:21:38,000 --> 00:21:39,800
We don’t need a screen,
we need a floor vacuum.

403
00:21:39,880 --> 00:21:41,120
No way.
-Yes way.

404
00:21:42,040 --> 00:21:43,320
Okay, so neither this nor that.

405
00:21:43,400 --> 00:21:44,480
Got it?
-Got it.

406
00:21:45,720 --> 00:21:47,280
So what are we doing with the money? Together?

407
00:21:49,160 --> 00:21:52,480
I don’t know, I think we can find something
that both you and I can enjoy.

408
00:21:55,040 --> 00:21:57,440
But I need 400 shekels from the money.
-For what?

409
00:21:57,520 --> 00:21:59,800
To get my lucky nail done at Lydia’s.

410
00:21:59,880 --> 00:22:01,960
I want to do a 24-inch nail.

411
00:22:14,720 --> 00:22:17,760
Are you underestimating?
-Not underestimating. Just don’t know...

412
00:22:17,840 --> 00:22:19,720
What a look you gave me, oh my God.

413
00:22:19,800 --> 00:22:20,680
I got scared.

414
00:22:20,760 --> 00:22:24,400
Shai is already waiting to see the... the mama machalta.

415
00:22:28,360 --> 00:22:30,880
Did you check the address of the delivery?

416
00:22:30,960 --> 00:22:32,840
Maybe it’s, maybe it’s...

417
00:22:34,440 --> 00:22:35,680
I don’t know, babe.

418
00:22:36,800 --> 00:22:37,640
Wait.

419
00:22:38,240 --> 00:22:40,880
Robot!
-I’ll talk to them.

420
00:22:44,360 --> 00:22:45,560
So sad.

421
00:22:46,440 --> 00:22:48,120
Like... it hurts.

422
00:22:48,960 --> 00:22:49,880
Sorry.

